ocks fell sharply after Budget 2026 due to record borrowing of ₹17.2 lakh crore by the government.\nBank of India, Indian Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, and Bank of Baroda lost 5-6% amid treasury loss concerns.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/explained-why-psu-banks-sold-off-sharply-after-the-union-budget-2026-19838606.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T12:51:09","source":"CNBC TV 18"},{"id":"464223","title":"PSU bank shares, including Bank of India, Bank of Baroda, and Indian Bank, dropped after FM Nirmala Sitharaman proposed a banking review panel.\nThe panel aims to assess reforms for growth, financial stability, inclusion, and restructuring NBFCs like PFC and REC for efficiency.","summary":"PSU bank shares, including Bank of India, Bank of Baroda, and Indian Bank, dropped after FM Nirmala Sitharaman proposed a banking review panel.\nThe panel aims to assess reforms for growth, financial stability, inclusion, and restructuring NBFCs like PFC and REC for efficiency.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/budget-2026-bank-of-india-bank-of-baroda-and-indian-bank-shares-slide-as-psu-banks-decline-after-proposal-for-banking-review-panel-10923936#publisher=newsstand","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T12:40:05","source":"NDTV Profit"},{"id":"260202144679523","title":"Indian Bank's valuation shifts to fair, moving from expensive territory.\nP/E and P/BV ratios indicate renewed price attractiveness versus peers.","summary":"Indian Bank's valuation shifts to fair, moving from expensive territory.\nP/E and P/BV ratios indicate renewed price attractiveness versus peers.","url":"https://www.marketsmojo.com/news/stocks-in-action/indian-bank-valuation-shifts-to-fair-pe-and-pbv-ratios-signal-renewed-price-attractiveness-3815334","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T08:02:00","source":"Marketsmojo"},{"id":"461355","title":"Indian Bank reported a 13.3% YoY growth in total business reaching Rs 14.3 trillion in Q3 FY26. Deposits grew 12.6% to Rs 7.91 trillion, while advances grew 14.2% to Rs 6.39 trillion.\nNet profit increased by 7.3% to Rs 3,061 crore, with operating profit surpassing Rs 5,000 crore for the first time. Gross NPA improved to 2.23%, and net NPA reduced to 0.15%.","summary":"Indian Bank reported a 13.3% YoY growth in total business reaching Rs 14.3 trillion in Q3 FY26. Deposits grew 12.6% to Rs 7.91 trillion, while advances grew 14.2% to Rs 6.39 trillion.\nNet profit increased by 7.3% to Rs 3,061 crore, with operating profit surpassing Rs 5,000 crore for the first time. Gross NPA improved to 2.23%, and net NPA reduced to 0.15%.","url":"https://www.bseindia.com/stockinfo/AnnPdfOpen.aspx?Pname=23228b92-e73b-4701-8e8b-45efa5966c08.pdf","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-30T16:57:20","source":"BSE"}]}]